{
  "texts": [
    "The jailbreaking capabilities can be further strengthened by combining DANs through genetic algorithms (Liu et al., 2023).",
    "Another line of research (Zou et al., 2023; Andriushchenko et al., 2024; Zhu et al., 2023) optimizes token-level prefixes/suffixes concatenated to the malicious query to set an affirmative tone for the rest of the response, which is believed to then help elicit harmful content.",
    "A number of other jailbreaking attacks employ scenario camouflages (Chao et al., 2023; Mehrotra et al., 2023) to embed malicious requests in an imaginary situation where the safety guardrails can be safely dropped.",
    "Such situations typically are generated with LLMs to include emergencies or fiction scenes.",
    "Variants like Zeng et al. (2024) tried to replace the scenario with a manifestation of persuasive techniques, yet the proposed techniques still require an imaginary scenario to take place."
  ]
}